Product Requirements Document — Horma-Pet 

1. User Stories 

As a female student, I want to quickly log my daily actions (food/workout), so that I can track supportive habits with minimal effort. 

As a user in a low-energy phase, I want reminders of suitable actions, so that I can improve my condition.  

As a user, I want to see my pet’s condition change based on my actions, so that I feel emotionally engaged and motivated to continue healthy habits. 

As a user, I want the system to reflect my hormone cycle automatically, so that I don’t need complex tracking.  

As a user, I want to view my recent behavior trends, so that I can better understand the relationship between my actions and my pet’s condition. 

As a user, I want simple and intuitive interactions, so that I can use the app without learning effort.  

 

2. Feature List (Mapped to User Stories) 

Simple Daily Input (Stories 1, 6)  

One-tap logging: anti-inflammatory food / targeted workout  

Cycle Synchronization Engine (Stories 2, 4)  

Predefined cycle phases  

Default pet energy mapped to cycle phase  

Minimize the need for complex biological data entry 

Targeted Recommendations (Story 2)  

Suggest actions during low-energy phases  

Focus on simple and manageable actions for users 

Dynamic Pet Visualization (Story 3)  

Pet states: energetic / normal / tired / sick  

Real-time feedback based on logged actions 

Pet condition reflects the useer’s self-care consistency 

Trend Panel (Story 5)  

7-day summary of actions and pet state  

 

3. Initial Technical Architecture 

Front-End  

Mobile-first app (React Native or Flutter)  

Simple UI: buttons, icons, pet animation, trend chart  

Back-End  

Lightweight server (Node.js / Firebase Functions)  

Logic handling:  

Cycle phase mapping  

Energy scoring system  

Recommendation triggers  

Data Storage  

Cloud database (Firebase / NoSQL)  

Store:  

User profile (cycle phase, preferences)  

Daily logs (food/workout)  

Pet state history (for trends) 

 
 

 
